title: A History of Architecture in England (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
A history of architecture in England, 2d ed by T. W. West.

pdf / 1966 / D. McKay Co. / 176 pages / 34.3 MB



A HISTORY OF ARCHITECTURE IN ENGLAND

is a concise survey of architectural development in this country from prehistoric times to the present day. The account of each period is preceded by a well-balanced summary of the political, economic, social and cultural trends of the time.

The text is amplified by a glossary of terms, and there is a short bibliography covering each architectural period, together with a list of representative buildings, at the end of each chapter. An important feature of the book is the use of attractive line-drawings, many of which the reader will be able to reproduce for himself without too much difficulty
